 accuracy (precision) and missed barcodes (recall) for linear barcodes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Some barcode types are naturally prone to false positives (e.g. MSI Plessey).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For those barcode types false positives can be drastically reduced (precision can be increased) by requiring that multiple scan-lines in the input scan to the same result.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, this stronger condition can lead to missed barcodes (lower recall).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Confirmation is avoided for barcode types, which are by design resistant to false positives, (e.g. Code128) to maximize recall.","type":"text"}]},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK":{"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Version: 8.0.4","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK","type":"topic","role":"collection","title":"ScanbotSDK"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode/none":{"title":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode.none","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationModeNone","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"none","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"No confirmation is required. This mode is the most prone to generating false positives.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode\/none","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkonedconfirmationmode\/none"}},"variantOverrides":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"\/identifier\/interfaceLanguage","value":"occ"},{"op":"replace","path":"\/metadata\/roleHeading","value":"Enumeration Case"},{"op":"replace","path":"\/metadata\/title","value":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationModeNone"},